    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesn't feel like \"stagnation\" though. stagnation implies something can grow back. this feels terminal. like the well didn't just run dry, it's actually just been filled in with concrete. i look at my work and i don't even recognize the person who made it. it's like i'm just a ghost haunting a life that doesn't belong to me anymore. what's the point of waiting around for a spark that's never coming back?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
